name: Bundle
description: A container for a collection of resources.

elements.name: id
elements.description: The logical id of the resource, as used in the URL for the resource. Once assigned, this value never changes.

elements.name: meta
elements.description: The metadata about the resource. This is content that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

constraints.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

elements.name: implicitRules
elements.short: A set of rules under which this content was created
elements.description: A reference to a set of rules that were followed when the resource was constructed, and which must be understood when processing the content. Often, this is a reference to an implementation guide that defines the special rules along with other profiles etc.

constraints.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

elements.name: language
elements.description: The base language in which the resource is written.

constraints.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

elements.name: identifier
elements.description: A persistent identifier for the bundle that won't change as a bundle is copied from server to server.

constraints.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

elements.name: type
elements.short: document | message | transaction | transaction-response | batch | batch-response | history | searchset | collection
elements.description: Indicates the purpose of this bundle - how it is intended to be used.

binding.description: Indicates the purpose of a bundle - how it is intended to be used.

elements.name: timestamp
elements.description: The date/time that the bundle was assembled - i.e. when the resources were placed in the bundle.

elements.name: total
elements.short: If search, the total number of matches
elements.description: If a set of search matches, this is the total number of entries of type 'match' across all pages in the search.  It does not include search.mode = 'include' or 'outcome' entries and it does not provide a count of the number of entries in the Bundle.

elements.name: fullUrl
elements.short: URI for resource (Absolute URL server address or URI for UUID/OID)
elements.description:
The Absolute URL for the resource.  The fullUrl SHALL NOT disagree with the id in the resource - i.e. if the fullUrl is not a urn:uuid, the URL shall be version-independent URL consistent with the Resource.id. The fullUrl is a version independent reference to the resource. The fullUrl element SHALL have a value except that: 
* fullUrl can be empty on a POST (although it does not need to when specifying a temporary id for reference in the bundle)
* Results from operations might involve resources that are not identified.
